"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting dynamic code generation**\\n\\nI'm noticing a potential issue with the `KEY_FACTORY` static initialization triggering dynamic code generation. This occurs when there's a native unsupported error caught before `Class.forName()`. The bytecode order seems to call `class$` before `KeyFactory.create`. So, it might be smart to ensure we're covering `Class.forName()`. However, if the native image preinitializes, that could change things. I think Java's dynamic report should address that too. Next, I should inspect the `build.gradle` root for the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_g5ulwUXDwab5z5jgnAITUTqd|fc_0d09153518c040920169fa6e38c6008190a92855a5bdcfe495", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport|dynamicAccess|dynamic-access\" -n build.gradle gradle tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/.gradle tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/build.gradle | head -200"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3815, "output": 905, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36976, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778019880414, "responseId": "resp_0d09153518c040920169fa6e292bd0819096cd768fdb958f53"}}
